  <h1>SMEG Dishwasher Repair — Los Angeles &amp; Southern California</h1>

  <p>SMEG is an Italian manufacturer from Guastalla — founded in 1948, they build kitchen appliances that are as much about design as function. The FAB retro refrigerators with the curved doors are everywhere in LA's design-conscious interiors, but SMEG also makes dishwashers: both the residential line that appears in Brentwood kitchens and Silver Lake bungalows alongside the retro fridge, and a professional commercial division (SMEG Professional) that supplies undercounter and hood-type dishwashers to Italian restaurants, design-forward cafés, and boutique hotels.</p>

  <p>In the LA market we service both SMEG lines. The residential SMEG dishwashers — the STL, PL, and DF series machines that match SMEG's kitchen aesthetic — are in premium homes and design-centric apartments throughout the Westside and Silver Lake. The SMEG Professional commercial undercounters and hood-types appear in Italian restaurant concepts and boutique hospitality properties. Both have SMEG's characteristic Italian engineering, and both have failure modes specific to LA's water conditions. $89 residential diagnostic / $120 commercial, both applied to the repair. Call <strong>{phone}</strong>.</p>

  <h2>SMEG Residential Dishwashers</h2>

  <h3>STL / PL / DF Series — Built-In and Freestanding</h3>
  <p>SMEG's residential dishwashers are the companion appliances to their iconic refrigerators. The STL series integrated dishwashers and PL series fully integrated models are in the same Beverly Hills and Brentwood kitchens that have Sub-Zero column refrigerators and Wolf ranges — the SMEG dishwasher chosen for its Italian design aesthetic and panel-front compatibility. The DF series freestanding dishwashers, including the retro-style models that match the FAB line, are in the design-conscious homes and apartments from Silver Lake to Malibu where the SMEG aesthetic is a deliberate choice.</p>
  <p>The most common residential SMEG service pattern in LA: scale buildup on the heating element from hard water is the dominant failure mode, same as every other residential dishwasher in this market. SMEG's residential machines also have a spray arm bearing failure pattern that we see with some regularity — the upper spray arm bearing develops wear and the arm stops rotating correctly, which shows up as inconsistent cleaning on upper-rack items. The symptom is gradual: dishes in one upper-rack section start coming out less clean, but the machine completes cycles and shows no error codes.</p>
  <p>SMEG residential parts are available through SMEG USA's North American distribution and through Italian parts suppliers. Common components — heating elements, spray arm assemblies, door seals, pump motors — are typically 3–5 business days.</p>
  <p><strong>Models:</strong> STL series, PL series, DF series, STLA series, LVFI series</p>

  <h3>SMEG Retro / FAB-Matching Dishwashers</h3>
  <p>SMEG's retro-style dishwashers in the iconic colors — pastel green, cream, red, black, cobalt blue — are in LA's design-forward interiors specifically because they match the FAB refrigerator line. These machines have the same internal engineering as SMEG's standard residential dishwashers, but the exterior panel and trim components are model-specific and color-matched. When a retro SMEG needs a door panel or trim component, that part has to match the specific color — replacement with a generic part defeats the purpose of having the SMEG. We order color-specific trim parts when needed.</p>

  <h2>SMEG Professional Commercial Dishwashers</h2>

  <h3>UD / UG Series — Commercial Undercounters &amp; Glasswashers</h3>
  <p>SMEG Professional's UD series undercounter dishwashers (UD505D, UD505H, UD512D, UD512H) and UG series glasswashers (UG405, UG505, UG510, UG610) are the commercial line — built for food service operation but retaining SMEG's Italian engineering approach. The "D" variants are chemical sanitizing (low temperature); the "H" variants are high-temperature with booster. Same HT/LT choice as on Jackson, Champion, and Classeq undercounters, with the same LA market implications: HT machines scale faster on the booster in LA hard water, LT machines need chemical sanitizer monitoring for health code compliance.</p>
  <p>SMEG Professional UG glasswashers appear in Italian restaurants and design-forward café concepts throughout LA — the brand is often specified by the same interior designers who put SMEG residential appliances in homes. The service approach is standard commercial glasswasher protocol with SMEG-specific parts sourcing: common wear items through SMEG Professional's commercial distribution, with 3–7 business day typical lead times.</p>
  <p><strong>Models:</strong> UD505D, UD505H, UD512D, UD512H, UG405D, UG405H, UG405SD, UG405SH, UG505D, UG505H, UG510D, UG510H, UG610D, UG610H</p>

  <h3>HTY / PT / CPT Series — Hood-Type &amp; Passthrough</h3>
  <p>SMEG Professional's HTY hood-type machines (HTY505D/H, HTY610D/H) and PT/CPT passthrough series are for mid-volume operations. These appear in Italian restaurants with higher volume than an undercounter can handle, and in boutique hotel kitchens that specified SMEG Professional as part of a kitchen buildout aligned with Italian brand aesthetics. Service follows standard hood-type commercial dishwasher protocol: booster element descaling (quarterly in LA water), door seal inspection, spray arm maintenance, chemical dosing calibration on D variants.</p>
  <p><strong>Models:</strong> HTY505D, HTY505H, HTY610D, HTY610H, PT110, PT220, PT330, CPT110, CPT220, CPT330</p>

  <h2>LA Hard Water &amp; SMEG — Residential and Commercial</h2>

  <p>SMEG equipment — both residential and professional — is engineered in Italy, where water hardness varies significantly by region. LA's 250–350 ppm TDS is at the high end of what the Italian market typically sees. The practical implication: SMEG's default maintenance intervals assume softer water than LA delivers, and scale-related failures happen faster in this market than SMEG's documentation suggests.</p>

  <p>For residential SMEG: descale every 2–3 months using a dishwasher-appropriate descaling tablet. For SMEG Professional commercial machines: monthly descaling on glasswashers and undercounters; quarterly on hood-type booster elements. We communicate this calibration to every SMEG operator we service — the maintenance schedule in the manual reflects Italian/European water conditions, not SoCal conditions.</p>

  <h2>Recent SMEG Service Calls</h2>

  <h3>"SMEG residential — upper spray arm not rotating, home Silver Lake"</h3>
  <p>Called by a homeowner with a SMEG STL built-in — dishes on the upper rack were coming out with residue in one corner quadrant, everything else clean. Classic upper spray arm bearing failure: the arm was rotating intermittently, not making full rotation. Replaced the upper spray arm assembly and bearing, verified full rotation through several cycles. Owner also had scale on the heating element from extended LA water operation — descaled while there. Total visit about 45 minutes. SMEG STL parts through SMEG USA, 4 business days.</p>

  <h3>"SMEG UG505H glasswasher — booster not reaching temperature, Italian restaurant Brentwood"</h3>
  <p>Italian restaurant on San Vicente called about their SMEG Professional UG505H glasswasher not completing cycles — machine was holding on the final rinse phase. Booster element scaled from approximately 8 months of LA water without descaling. Full descale with citric acid solution, verified 180°F final rinse temperature post-service, set the restaurant on monthly descaling. The chef had been maintaining the machine on the SMEG manual's annual descaling schedule, which is calibrated for Italian water hardness, not LA's.</p>

  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <p><strong>Do you service both residential and commercial SMEG dishwashers?</strong><br>
  Yes. We service SMEG residential (STL, PL, DF, retro series) and SMEG Professional commercial (UD, UG, HTY, PT, CPT series) throughout LA and SoCal. $89 diagnostic for residential, $120 for commercial — both applied to the repair.</p>

  <p><strong>My SMEG retro dishwasher needs a replacement door panel — can you match the color?</strong><br>
  Yes. SMEG retro exterior components are color-specific. We order color-matched trim and panel parts through SMEG USA's parts network. Lead times for color-specific retro components are typically 5–10 business days depending on availability.</p>

  <p><strong>How often should SMEG equipment be descaled in Los Angeles?</strong><br>
  Residential: every 2–3 months with descaling tablets. Commercial glasswashers and undercounters: monthly. Commercial hood-type booster elements: quarterly. SMEG's manual schedules are calibrated for Italian water conditions which are softer than LA's 250–350 ppm. The manual intervals are too long for this market.</p>

  <p><strong>What is your diagnostic fee?</strong><br>
  $89 residential, $120 commercial — both applied to the repair when you proceed. On-site quote, what we quote is on the invoice.</p>

